But official events also have political overtones.
At the event, the president gave an impetus to the reform of health care reform underway in the Senate, and he propagated efforts to curb government rules.
The use of the aircraft, known as Marine One or Air Force One, for politically beneficial purposes is hardly a new phenomenon.
Presidents are required to use them for the trip.
But to request their use only for a photo surgery is unusual.
Trump conducted an investigation in February when the presidential plane provided taxi services against the backdrop of his first campaign rally in Melbourne, Florida, and his Twitter account is full of reports complaining about the use of the presidential plane by his predecessor.
"The White House is enthusiastic about the show "Made In America" - which shows products from all 50 states made by American workers using American materials," White House deputy press secretary Lindsay Walters said.
HMX-1 crews frequently conduct training flights in the area around Washington and the South Lawn to drop the US president at the White House with precise centimeters.
