Roll backwards: The city hires 46 kitchen aids
The city organizes the daycare lunch again itself.
With fixed contact persons for the children and an assignment to the team.
In the city's daycare centers, the clock is turned back.
To the 1. In September, the city of Krefeld takes over the food supply in the municipal day-care facilities (Kitas) again on its own.
For Sonja Pommeranz, deputy head of the department of youth welfare, this is good news: "We were all very pleased".
Cooking continues to be done: a caterer takes over this task and delivers freshly cooked chilled food.
The city operates 46 day-care centers in the Krefeld area, in 44 the children get a hot meal at lunchtime.
In the past daycare year, 2800 children each sat at the tables, and the need is growing steadily.
"Meanwhile, not only children who are looked after 45 hours a week eat lunch in the day-care center," explains Pommeranz.
"The offer is also valid in 35-hour care if children stay until 2pm."
46 part-time workers have from the first. September Kitchen service: They heat the delivered food, supplement them with salad, raw food and fruit, portion the meal individually, give out the food, clear, rinse and clean the kitchen.
"The employees are firmly assigned to a daycare center," says Pommeranz.
The size - there are two-group as well as seven-group facilities - decides the hourly scope.
"The kitchen assistants are now firmly part of the day-care team," says Pommeranz with satisfaction.
"So they are much more involved and it is easier for the daycare management to implement pedagogical concepts".
Because that's also what it's all about: healthy eating and cooking lessons.
"The children should help to prepare the food."
The direct connection of the kitchen staff to the team makes sense.
Also for the children.
“They have a well-known force in daycare, a person who is familiar to them, and not constantly changing people.”
This continuity is important for the children.
The cleaning of the day-care rooms - so far also the task of the kitchen staff - will be carried out by special cleaning staff in the future.
This variant - the separation of cleaning and kitchen service - has not only the quality improvement of the kitchen performance but also the charm that it has highlighted in the cost comparison between self-directing and third-party allocation for the city as the most economical, according to the press office.
And this, although 46 part-time workers are rehired.
"But these hours are not so important for around 750 people in the education area," says Sonja Pommeranz.
