Do you know such methods of punishment?
Of course, I think each of us who was born before 1968.
I, too, have experienced this in a secular school, a state high school.
Compared to what this report is actually about, namely the horrific sexual abuse and the excesses of violence in preschool, these are, of course, trivial.
One wonders whether it is not more to do with his notoriety and his role as the brother of Benedict XVI, that many media just threw themselves on him.
Many of the Bavarian Popes, who have never understood him, are still working hard.
But the truth is that the report relieves Georg Ratzinger in every way!
In the media, a lot has been reported in connection with the report on the topic of abuse at the Regensburger Domspatzen.
Is Georg Ratzinger also charged with any involvement or co-scrutiny with regard to sexual abuse in the final report?
Michael Hesemann: Clearly no.
Not a single one of the 67 victims of sexual assault claims to have confided in the cathedral chapel master.
Not even the parents were initiated.
"I never dared to talk to my father or my mother about it," said one person on behalf of the others, "It was all very embarrassing to me."
The real problem with the investigation of sexual abuse was and still is that most of the victims are silent out of shame.
If they did not even confide in parents and siblings, then certainly not to a choir director, who would have been a colleague of the perpetrators professionally.
How do the Domspatzen students rate Ratzinger’s role in view of the abuse cases?
Michael Hesemann: A student interviewed put it this way: "With regard to sexual abuse ... I do not see ... a case in which he (Georg Ratzinger) of all people would have had timely findings and could have stopped the respective perpetrator.
